# Course Structure

Shared types & barrel: `apps/course/src/content/course/sections.ts` (re-exports Achilles as default)
Shared types & utilities: `apps/course/src/content/course/section-types.ts`

## Achilles Rupture Course

Content root: `apps/course/src/content/course/achilles-rupture/`
Sections: `apps/course/src/content/course/achilles-rupture/sections.ts`

## 00-practical (cross-cutting, not phase-specific)

- `recovery-roadmap.tsx`: 4-stage overview (Immobilisation → Transition → Capacity → Return to Sport)
- `first-week-checklist.tsx`: Week 1 symptoms, red flags, essential purchases
- `pain-management-throughout-recovery.tsx`: Pain at each stage, normal vs concerning, DVT vs calf pain
- `mental-health-recovery.tsx`: Anxiety, depression, kinesiophobia, when to seek help
- `driving-guidelines.tsx`: When to drive, left vs right leg, insurance
- `appendix-1-faqs.tsx`: Central FAQ reference from all lessons
- `course-completion.tsx` / `course-feedback.tsx`: Non-medical

## 01-emergency (Week 0-1)

- `emergency-care.tsx`: A&E, plantarflexion, Simmonds/Thompson test, immobilisation
- `blood-clot-prevention.tsx`: DVT/PE risk, VTE prophylaxis, blood thinners, warning signs

## 02-early-treatment (Weeks 1-3)

- `treatment-decision.tsx`: UKSTAR trial, surgery vs non-surgical, risks/benefits
- `specialist-appointment.tsx`: History, Simmonds test, ultrasound vs MRI, gap measurement
- `choosing-your-boot.tsx`: Aircast vs VACOped, Thetis night splint, costs
- `post-surgery-care.tsx`: Wound care, infection signs, scar massage (surgical patients only)

## 03-boot-phase (Weeks 3-10)

- `your-walking-boot.tsx`: How Aircast (wedges) and VACOped (hinge) work
- `boot-adjustment-and-care.tsx`: Fit, straps, air cells, maintenance
- `boot-progression-protocol.tsx`: Angle reduction from week 5, mobilisation, weightbearing
- `wedge-removal.tsx`: When/how to remove wedges, warning signs
- `healing-process.tsx`: Inflammation → proliferation → remodelling, re-rupture vs elongation
- `sleeping-with-boot.tsx`: Night splint, positioning, temperature, 24/7 protection
- `crutches-and-mobility.tsx`: Crutch use, EVENup, knee scooters, iWalk
- `building-strength-in-boot.tsx`: Stage 1 exercises from Week 6 (seated calf raises with protection)
- `nutrition-for-healing.tsx`: Protein, vitamin C, hydration, collagen
- `washing-and-hygiene.tsx`: Bathroom safety, antifungal, merino socks, swelling
- `final-boot-phase.tsx`: Remodelling, tendon strength at Week 8, preparing for physio

## 04-transition (Weeks 10-12)

- `boot-transition.tsx`: When to leave boot, weaning, shoe choice, heel lifts
- `post-boot-period.tsx`: Boot removal criteria, gradual weaning, first steps
- `post-boot-challenges.tsx`: Stiffness, swelling, avoiding aggressive stretching (elongation risk)
- `scar-management.tsx`: Scar tissue, massage, bio-oil, sun protection

## 05-physiotherapy (Weeks 10-24)

- `starting-physio.tsx`: First session, Stage 2 goals (15+ double-leg heel raises, 1.4x BW MVIC)
- `key-exercises.tsx`: Seated calf raises, standing heel raises, towel stretch, resistance bands, balance
- `walking-properly.tsx`: Heel-to-toe gait, correcting limp, retro walking, heel lifts
- `progressive-strengthening.tsx`: Single-leg targets (15 then 25 reps), LSI 90%, deficit heel raises

## 06-recovery (Weeks 12-25)

- `building-cardio.tsx`: Swimming, bike, elliptical, walk-jog progression
- `swimming-and-water-activities.tsx`: When to start (weeks 12-14), pool walking, strokes
- `returning-to-life.tsx`: Work (desk vs physical), household tasks, travel
- `functional-milestones.tsx`: Pain-free walking, 25+ heel raises, balance, stairs (Stage 3 exit)

## 07-advanced (Weeks 25+)

- `starting-to-run.tsx`: Criteria, walk-jog progression, form, surface choice
- `plyometrics.tsx`: When to start, pogo jumps → sport-specific, landing technique
- `return-to-sport.tsx`: 85% symmetry rule, modified → full participation, 70-80% return rates

## 08-long-term (6+ months)

- `six-month-milestone.tsx`: Tendon status, return-to-sport criteria, psychological readiness
- `preventing-rerupture.tsx`: 3-5% risk, ongoing strengthening, warm-ups, warning signs
- `other-leg.tsx`: ~5% contralateral rupture risk
- `when-things-dont-go-to-plan.tsx`: Slow progress, elongation, when to seek further opinion
- `new-normal.tsx`: Permanent changes (thickening, asymmetry), long-term care

## Plantar Fasciitis Course

Content root: `apps/course/src/content/course/plantar-fasciitis/`
Sections: `apps/course/src/content/course/plantar-fasciitis/sections.ts`

### 00-understanding

- `introduction.tsx`: Why does my heel hurt, self-limiting nature, guide aims
- `common-myths.tsx`: It will never go away, I need injection/surgery, etc.
- `anatomy.tsx`: Calcaneum, calf muscles, Achilles tendon, plantar fascia (hammock analogy)
- `what-went-wrong.tsx`: Daily wear vs repair balance, collagen fraying, inflammation
- `why-it-persists.tsx`: The Four O's – Overuse, Overweight, Overtight, Over-21

### 01-level-1-foundation (allow 3 months)

- `treatment-overview.tsx`: Three-level approach, no magic cures, discipline
- `rest-and-weight-management.tsx`: Activity modification, weight loss rationale
- `stretching-programme.tsx`: Why stretching is the cornerstone
- `slant-board-guide.tsx`: Detailed slant board usage, rationale, choices
- `weekly-progression.tsx`: Weeks 1–6+ structured plan
- `footwear-and-insoles.tsx`: Supportive shoes, Fit-flops/Vionic/OOFOS, insoles
- `toe-stretches-and-night-splints.tsx`: Morning toe stretch, Strasburg sock, Dorsiwedge
- `maintaining-progress.tsx`: Don't stop stretching, preventative maintenance

### 02-level-2-further-treatment (after 3+ months)

- `when-to-seek-help.tsx`: When Level 1 hasn't worked, next steps
- `scans-and-diagnosis.tsx`: Ultrasound vs MRI, differential diagnoses
- `steroid-injections.tsx`: Short-term benefit only (McMillan RCT), risks
- `shockwave-therapy.tsx`: ESWL mechanism, protocol, 60% success rate
- `prp-injections.tsx`: Product Rich in Placebo – evidence review

### 03-level-3-surgery (rare, after 12+ months)

- `surgery-overview.tsx`: When surgery is considered, two approaches
- `gastrocnemius-recession.tsx`: Calf release rationale, evidence, outcomes
- `plantar-fascia-release.tsx`: Historical popularity, why now limited, arch instability risk

## FAQ pages (website)

Location: `apps/website/src/mains/FAQs/` (thin wrappers) → `apps/website/src/sections/FAQs/` (actual content)

- `is-my-achilles-ruptured`: Symptoms, diagnosis, differential (tennis leg)
- `what-happens-if-my-achilles-is-ruptured`: A&E, specialist, ultrasound, boot, blood thinners
- `achilles-tear-treatment`: Surgery vs non-surgical, pain types, scar healing
- `achilles-rupture-timeline`: Week-by-week timeline with guide phase links
- `achilles-rupture-rehabilitation`: Exercise phases, rehab timeline, driving, running
- `torn-achilles-recovery`: Boot vs cast, sleeping, healing time, partial tears
- `life-after-achilles-rupture`: Return to sport/work, walking, re-rupture prevention

## Blog articles

